OL,3,C28 recommendations to strengthen
OL,4,Csafeguarding in assisted dying
OL,5,Cproposals
OL,7,FConcerns over coercion, decision-
OL,8,Fmaking capacity, and palliative care
OL,9,Fhave been highlighted by a scrutiny
OL,10,Fpanel evaluating Jersey's draft
OL,11,FAssisted Dying legislation.
OL,13,FAfter months of work, the Assisted
OL,14,FDying Review Panel has published key
OL,15,Ffindings and 28 recommendations ahead
OL,16,Fof States Members debating the draft
OL,17,Flaw on Tuesday 24 February.
OL,19,FWhile the panel said the legislation
OL,20,Fis 'robust', there are still concerns
OL,21,Fthat safeguards are not strong enough.
