OL,4,Csafeguarding in assisted dying
OL,5,Cproposals
OL,7,FFor example, approving the bill would
OL,8,Fintroduce 'a waiver of future
OL,9,Fcapacity', which an individual could
OL,10,Fsign to allow for their assisted death
OL,11,Fto proceed - if their capacity to
OL,12,Fconsent is lost due to their illness
OL,13,Flater in the process.
OL,15,FHowever, the Panel warns that this
OL,16,Fraises "significant ethical and
OL,17,Fpractical concerns".
