OL,3,C28 recommendations to strengthen
OL,4,Csafeguarding in assisted dying
OL,5,Cproposals
OL,7,FRecent proposals in England, Scotland,
OL,8,Fand the Isle of Man ensure the final
OL,9,Fdecision must be made consciously by
OL,10,Fthe individual.
OL,12,FOn this, the Panel has reclarified
OL,13,Fwhether practitioners would be
OL,14,Fcomfortable administering approved
OL,15,Fdrugs with a waiver in place and to
OL,16,Ffurther consult on whether there is
OL,17,Fenough public support.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G3/16
