OL,3,C28 recommendations to strengthen
OL,4,Csafeguarding in assisted dying
OL,5,Cproposals
OL,7,FCurrently, an amendment would
OL,8,Fintroduce a statutory right for an
OL,9,Findividual to pause the assisted dying
OL,10,Fprocess to pursue palliative care
OL,11,Fthrough an "appropriately-qualified
OL,12,Fhealth professional", which the Panel
OL,13,Fapproves.
OL,15,FHowever, they recommend a change to
OL,16,Fallow palliative care specialists to
OL,17,Fbe considered "suitably qualified" for
OL,18,Fbetter safeguarding.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G6/16
