OL,3,C28 recommendations to strengthen
OL,4,Csafeguarding in assisted dying
OL,5,Cproposals
OL,7,FThe Panel has also recommended that
OL,8,Fthere is "a clear appeals and dispute-
OL,9,Fresolution mechanism" for families,
OL,10,Fcarers, and professionals to address
OL,11,Fconcerns.
OL,13,FDetailed guidance should also be given
OL,14,Fon the requirements of assessing
OL,15,Fdoctors, informing individuals of all
OL,16,Ftreatment and care options, and how
OL,17,Findividuals can be referred to end-of-
OL,18,Flife and palliative care support.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G7/16
