OL,3,C28 recommendations to strengthen
OL,4,Csafeguarding in assisted dying
OL,5,Cproposals
OL,7,FThe Panel recommends that the minimum
OL,8,Frequirements for any practitioner
OL,9,Fadministering assisted dying care be
OL,10,Fset out fully before the draft Law is
OL,11,Fimplemented, including robust criteria
OL,12,Ffor assessing physical incapacity.
OL,14,FConcerning 'the waiver of future
OL,15,Fcapacity', it is recommended that the
OL,16,Fgovernment survey practitioners
OL,17,Ffurther on whether they would
OL,18,Fadminister approved drugs in cases
OL,19,Fwhere a waiver is exercised.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G9/16
