OL,3,C28 recommendations to strengthen
OL,4,Csafeguarding in assisted dying
OL,5,Cproposals
OL,7,FIf an assisted dying practitioner is
OL,8,Fnot willing to perform an assisted
OL,9,Fdeath when a waiver is signed, this
OL,10,Fshould be made clear earlier in the
OL,11,Fassisted dying process.
OL,13,FIt also recommends clarification on
OL,14,Fwhat happens to an individual who has
OL,15,Fthe capacity to pause the assisted
OL,16,Fdying process on the date they are due
OL,17,Fto give final consent.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws        G10/16
