OL,5,Cproposals
OL,7,FThe Panel also asks that the Minister
OL,8,Ffor Health and Social Services should
OL,9,Factively engage with marginalised
OL,10,Fgroups across the island to ensure all
OL,11,Fcommunities understand what the law
OL,12,Fwill entail.
OL,14,FOne amendment lodged by the Panel
OL,15,Foutlines how written information on
OL,16,Fassisted dying could be provided
OL,17,Fwithin GP surgeries. They recommend
OL,18,Fthat this guidance be provided only in
OL,19,Fthe presence of a health professional.
